<div id="review_1537288116" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1537288116" />
    <a title="Ulysse" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/46226399-ulysse"><img alt="Ulysse" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1640429410p2/46226399.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1537288116?book_show_action=true">Feb 04, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ulysse" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ulysse" href="/user/show/46226399-ulysse">Ulysse</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9782070307661" href="/book/show/46983.Les_Fleurs_du_Mal">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46226399-ulysse?shelf=books-to-line-my-coffin-with">books-to-line-my-coffin-with</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46226399-ulysse?shelf=i-think-it-s-poetry">i-think-it-s-poetry</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46226399-ulysse?shelf=read-twice-or-more">read-twice-or-more</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46226399-ulysse?shelf=19th-century">19th-century</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46226399-ulysse?shelf=2021">2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46226399-ulysse?shelf=read-in-fran%C3%A7ais">read-in-français</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46226399-ulysse?shelf=poesie-gallimard">poesie-gallimard</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1537288116" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17191299790718100307">Dear Charles,<br/><br/>I’m flattered to be your muse, I really am. How many women can say they’ve inspired a genius to write poems about them, poems that will be read and loved hundreds of years from now? You have immortalized me in perfect rhymes, and thanks to you I shall always be remembered as a flower of evil. I am your dark lady, your giantess, your pussy cat, your vampire, your lovely corpse, and what not. But while we’re waiting for eternity, could you please take out the trash and fix that window</span>
  <span id="freeText17191299790718100307" style="display:none">Dear Charles,<br /><br />I’m flattered to be your muse, I really am. How many women can say they’ve inspired a genius to write poems about them, poems that will be read and loved hundreds of years from now? You have immortalized me in perfect rhymes, and thanks to you I shall always be remembered as a flower of evil. I am your dark lady, your giantess, your pussy cat, your vampire, your lovely corpse, and what not. But while we’re waiting for eternity, could you please take out the trash and fix that window you broke last month and lower the toilet seat when you’re finished? Could you also refrain from smoking opium before every job interview? You’re almost forty, for Pete’s sake. Don’t you think it’s time you became more responsible and got a real job? Writing poems is all very fine and I do not question your talent, but will these poems pay the bills? I highly doubt it. I’m not getting any younger either, you know, and standing out in the streets of Paris night after night with the rain pouring down is really not my idea of fun. I’d like to go back to school and study interior decorating or psychology. I’d like to do something with my life other than just be some guy’s fantasy. You do seem to have serious commitment issues, Charles. Every time I mention the possibility of our having a child together, you look at me like I've just read you a poem by Alfred de Musset. How long do I have to sit here waiting for you to get your act together? Maybe your exile to Brussels isn’t such a bad idea. Maybe what we need is a break. Or maybe you and I have simply reached the end of the road? I don't know. It’s up to you to decide, Charles. After all, <i>you’re</i> the genius here. The question is: how inspired <i>are</i> you to save our love from dissolution?<br /><br />Yours,<br /><br />Jeanne Duval</span>
  <a data-text-id="17191299790718100307" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


